==English==
===Noun===
'''kneecapping''' (''[[countable]] and [[uncountable]]''; ''plural'' '''kneecappings''')

#(''uncountable'') The act of destroying the [[kneecap]]s of (a person), usually by shooting at the knees, as a punishment carried out by criminals or terrorists.
#:''There have been five reports of kneecapping this month.''
#(''countable'') An act of this type of punishment.
#:''The mafiosi punished the informer by giving him a kneecapping.''